The paper discusses social tagging systems and their use in recommender systems, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses network-based, tensor-based, and topic-based approaches, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper touches on user behavior and preferences, which is relevant to the social computing (cs.SOC) sub-category.
